# Phase Kickoff Assessment

At phase start:

1. Run **`pnpm exec wk run phase-kickoff-readiness`** for the target **`phaseKey`** (or `'{}'` for workspace canonical phase). Read **`data.passed`** and remediate **`data.findings`** per **`.ai/runbooks/phase-kickoff-readiness.md`** — do **not** use **`docs/maintainers/`** for kickoff procedure. Copy-paste argv table: **`.ai/AGENT-CLI-MAP.extended.md`** → **Phase kickoff readiness (Tier C)**.
2. Align canonical workspace phase with task-engine state: MCP first when fresh, otherwise **`pnpm exec wk run get-workspace-status`** + **`phase-status`**. Per-task phase buckets use **`phaseKey`** on tasks; workspace current phase uses **`kit_workspace_status`**. Operator **Sprint** wording: **`.ai/TERMS.md`** `term|name=sprint|…`.
3. Confirm the task-engine ready queue: MCP first when fresh; otherwise **`workspace-kit run get-ready-queue`** or **`list-tasks '{"status":"ready","phaseKey":"<N>"}'`**.
4. Dry-run rollover when changing workspace phase: **`set-current-phase`** with **`dryRun:true`** after kickoff passes (or when enforcement is advisory-only).
5. Define evidence expectations for phase-exit confidence (**`phase-delivery-preflight`**, **`phase-closeout-readiness`** at closeout).
6. Identify human-only decisions early; record blockers on workspace status when needed.
